rComments: One of my favourite profs. Easy to reach and gives good feedback
Fun class and easy if you attend and follow along. Participation is key!
Easy to follow, fun to participate and great teacher! Highly recommend.
Very caring and amazing teacher! I've been lucky to have her as my teacher for two semesters now. Great course material and enjoyable class.

One of the best FLS profs I've had. Grading schemes are very clear, and feedback given is clear and thorough. Workload was less than average for language courses. Clearly cares about her students and is flexible with due dates if issues arise. 3 small individual assignments, 25% group presentation and final exam.

Sheila is awesome. The class was interesting and easy. Sheila made it interesting and is very passionate. Shes also super willing to meet with students outside of class and is very accessible by email and accommodating. She extends due dates and the projects and the exam was small and easy. Highly recommend this class with Sheila!
Sheila is an absolute gem! Gives time to every student. She has clear rubrics/expectations and is simply refreshing as she genuinely cares!

She's the best. So sweet and accommodating. Her assignments are interesting and it makes class fun. She never makes you feel stupid, rather helps you where you need it. I absolutely love her and she made FLS so enjoyable for me. TAKE HER CLASS!

love this prof!! she's so sweet, funny, and VERY accommodating when you need help. 3 tests and a final. the only downsides are that she's sometimes unorganized, and that her tests are ridiculously long for the time allotted (but she will give extra time if you ask!). other than that, you will be fine! would totally take this prof again! :)

Professor Scott was extremely kind throughout the semester and offered redos on exams and dictations. She was very accessible outside her office hours. Her lessons are very straightforward. Your French level will significantly increase. I learned more in one week in her class than I did in FLS 1512.

I really enjoyed professor Scott and this course. While she can be very disorganized(especially with her calendar) she is very open to questions and all you have to do is ask if something seems unclear and she will help you and make it more clear. She is a very caring professor and loves to throw humor into her lectures. I highly recommend her!
Sheila was a very caring professor. She is aware of the other courses we are taking and thus, she does not make the exams very demanding. She prepared us very well and she was very accessible.

I loved this Professor. I missed the first month and a half of the semester for a disability, but she made the slides accessible on Brightspace and provided a review sheet so that I could do well in the class. She is very understanding and a great teacher. I would recommend her.
the course was super unorganized but she's really nice and helpful, i would suggest making use of her office hours as often as possible

Prof. Scott is by far my favourite prof at Ottawa U. She's such a sweetheart and she always makes sure you understand what she's talking about. I'm not even required to take this course and out of all the prof's that I've had, Prof. Scott is the most organized and she teaches the only class I can go to without falling asleep.

The worst professor I have ever had. A nice person I'm sure, but totally unqualified to teach this class. She seems to have a lot of trouble understanding the material and her tests reflect this poor understanding. The majority of the marks are given for irrelevant material given in asides, very little for knowledge of concepts.
good teacher, fun, knows her stuff

She is so wonderful!! I went into her class not remembering most of my french, but she is soo patient and i'm actually learning more french than i did in all of elementary. she likes to make sure we all understand and are learning, and he class is very easy if u just practice a little! Highly recomend her!

Loved her class even though it was grammar. Sheila was always available and a lot of help during office hours. Used alot of games but they helped practice and learn the material. I would definantly take another class with her!

Awesome professor...had great discussions in her FLS course on a variety of issues...easy to get a great mark with her...her tests are almost exactly what she covers in class... and the TP's were easy

What an amzing teacher!  For the first time in 4 years I have actually enjoyed a linguistics class, and it's all because of her.  She is really sweet and helpful.  I highly recommend taking anything that she teaches.
excellent prof. makes syntax really fun. draws out trees step by step. talks quiet sometimes, but great classes. tests test what she teaches.
Prof Scott made syntax really interesting, not to mention informative. I highly recommend taking classes that she teaches!
Excellent teacher who is genuinely interested in helping students understand the potentially difficult material.
She is so sweet, go see her if you don't understand, she will help you. The material is boring, but that's not her fault, I felt like she was one of us. I am so happy I took a class with her.

La classe était incroyablement plate car elle ne faisait que traduire MOT POUR MOT le livre (qui était en Anglais)...Dommage car elle est bien gentille! Elle n'a aucun contrôle sur la classe et se trompe souvent par contre...
Très gentille et motivee... Elle veut nous faire reussir!!
You can tell she loves to teach. What a great teacher!
What a nice lady! course material was kind of dry, but she made it as fun as possible :) Seems to really like teaching! Great prof!
she does her best with the course the material is not that interesting, very helpful, wants you to do good!
Very nice. Gives easy assignments. Not too sure the point of the class though...
